As‑shot white balance gains (R, G, B) are stored in the Leica MOV container
metadata. The GIOP IDT applies the inverse of these gains before the matrix.

5. ISO AND SENSOR CHARACTERISTICS
  Leica SL cameras use a standard CMOS sensor without dual native ISO;
  ISO values above base are implemented via digital gain.

  Base ISO (native): 100 (SL2/SL3), 400 (SL2‑S)
  Effective video ISO range: 100–12800 (extended)
  Read noise (base): ~1.8 e⁻ (SL2‑S), ~2.0 e⁻ (SL2)
  Full well capacity (base): ~45,000 e⁻
  Dynamic range (SNR=1): ~13.5 stops (SL2), ~14.2 stops (SL2‑S)

  The IDT is ISO‑agnostic; the same inverse L‑Log and matrix apply
  regardless of ISO. ISO metadata is used only for noise profiling.

6. METADATA HANDLING
  Leica clips (MOV container) carry:
    - Bit depth (10‑bit internal / 12‑bit external)
    - ISO
    - White balance
    - Lens data (L‑mount metadata)
  The GIOP IDT reads bit depth to select correct inverse constants.
  If metadata is absent, the IDT defaults to 10‑bit L‑Log and Daylight.

